With Conda (Linux or Windows):

1. Create a new environment: conda create --name pySIGEN python=3.6 numpy pillow
2. Activate environment: source activate pySIGEN (Linux) or activate pySIGEN (Windows)
3. Install pySIGEN: pip install <path to pySIGEN repository>
4. Install SIGEN and its dependencies from https://sites.google.com/site/sigenproject/downloads.
5. Modify the variables sigenMorphExtractor and sigenSmoothing to point to
"MorphExtractorCL.exe" and "swcsmoothing.exe" respectively

Without Conda, with pip and virtualenvwrapper (only for Linux, Mac):

1. Create a new environment: mkvirtualenv pySIGEN
2. Activate environment: workon pySIGEN
3. Install pySIGEN: pip install <path to pySIGEN repository>
4. Install SIGEN and its dependencies from https://sites.google.com/site/sigenproject/downloads.
5. Modify the variables sigenMorphExtractor and sigenSmoothing to point to
"MorphExtractorCL.exe" and "swcsmoothing.exe" respectively


See file USAGE on how to use.